                     f.  Manager, Knowledge and Technology Transfer Office.  The Manager of the


                         Knowledge  and  Technology  Transfer  Office  has  the  following  duties  and

                         responsibilities:

                       •  Facilitate  the  establishment  of  a  network  of  companies  connected  to  the

                           University  utilizing  the    generated  technology  from  researches  and/or

                           university researchers (spin-off) to enhance prospects of further development;


                       •  Facilitate  the  creation  of  new  funding  support  from  sponsored  research  or

                           consulting opportunities;

                       •  Provide  assistance  on  all  areas  related  to  entrepreneurship  and

                           commercialization  of  technology  with  filed  intellectual  property  (IP)  and  IP

                           rights;


                       •  Facilitate net royalty generation for the University and collaborating partners;

                       •  Coordinate with higher authorities on the selection of technical experts who will

                           assist in the screening of patentable materials, technology readiness level and

                           investment readiness level;

                       •  Provide profile of CvSU technology with IP to potential investors;


                       •  Facilitate and submit requirements to DOST for fairness opinion report;
